</head><body><div id="root"><page locale="en" path="speakthewords" title="Speak The Words " description="Discover how to find, create, and use activities with H5P's speech recognition software " :tags="[{&quot;tag&quot;:&quot;speaking task&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;speaking task&quot;},{&quot;tag&quot;:&quot;speaking&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;speaking&quot;},{&quot;tag&quot;:&quot;speaking practice&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;speaking practice&quot;},{&quot;tag&quot;:&quot;speak the words&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;speak the words&quot;}]" created-at="2020-04-24T01:35:00.070Z" updated-at="2020-08-06T02:56:58.866Z" author-name="Joliene" :author-id="4" editor="ckeditor" :is-published="true" toc="" :page-id="10" sidebar="" nav-mode="MIXED" comments-enabled effective-permissions="" edit-shortcuts="" filename="en/speakthewords.html"><template slot="contents"><div><h1 id="speak-the-words-overview" class="toc-header"><a class="toc-anchor" href="speakthewords#speak-the-words-overview">¶</a> <span class="text-huge">Speak the Words: Overview </span></h1><div>
</div><p> </p><div>
</div><figure class="image image_resized image-style-align-right" style="width:32.53%;"><img src="../speak_the_words_example.png">
  <figcaption><span class="text-huge">Example Speak the Words Activity</span></figcaption>
</figure><div>
</div><p><span class="text-huge">&quot;</span><a href="https://h5p.org/speak-the-words" class="is-external-link"><span class="text-huge">Speak The Words</span></a><span class="text-huge">&quot; uses speech recognition software that allows learners to verbally respond to a question in ANVILL. The learners&apos; answer has to match whatever you, the instructor, decide is the correct answer.</span></p><div>
</div><p><span class="text-huge">You can either create and embed a single Speak the Words question in your lesson, </span></p><div>
</div><p><span class="text-huge">or use a &quot;Speak the Words Set&quot; to create multiple questions as one activity. Navigate here for an </span><a href="https://h5p.org/speak-the-words-set" class="is-external-link"><span class="text-huge">example of a Speak the Words Set based activity</span></a><span class="text-huge">.</span><br> </p><div>
</div><h2 id="important-browser-compatibility" class="toc-header"><a class="toc-anchor" href="speakthewords#important-browser-compatibility">¶</a> <span class="text-huge"><strong>Important</strong>: Browser Compatibility</span></h2><div>
</div><ul>
  <li><span class="text-huge">&quot;Speak the Words&quot; activities are <strong>only Google Chrome</strong> compatible.</span></li>
  <li><span class="text-huge">You can </span><a href="https://support.google.com/chrome/answer/95346?co=GENIE.Platform%3DDesktop&amp;hl=en" class="is-external-link"><span class="text-huge">download and install Google Chrome for free</span></a><span class="text-huge"> on Windows, Mac, or Linux</span></li>
</ul><div>
</div><h1 id="page-contents" class="toc-header"><a class="toc-anchor" href="speakthewords#page-contents">¶</a> <span class="text-huge">Page Contents </span></h1><div>
</div><figure class="image image_resized image-style-align-left" style="width:14.26%;"><img src="../speak_the_words.png"></figure><div>
</div><p><span class="text-huge"><strong>  Section 1:</strong></span><br><span class="text-huge">  Add and create a &quot;Speak the Words&quot; activity or &quot;Speak the Words Set&quot; in your lesson</span></p><div>
</div><p><span class="text-huge"><strong>  Section 2: </strong></span><br><span class="text-huge">  Create content in your  &quot;Speak the Words&quot; question and a &quot;Speak the Words Set&quot; of questions</span></p><div>
</div><h1 id="h-1-access-speak-the-words-in-lesson" class="toc-header"><a class="toc-anchor" href="speakthewords#h-1-access-speak-the-words-in-lesson">¶</a> <br><br><span class="text-huge">1. Access &quot;Speak The Words&quot; in Lesson</span></h1><div>
</div><p><span class="text-huge">You have two options. To create a &quot;Speak The Words&quot; or &quot;Speak The Words Set&quot; activity. The first, &quot;Speak the Words,&quot; allows you to create one question prompt. The second, &quot;Speak The Words Set,&quot; allows you to create more than one prompt. </span></p><div>
</div><ol>
  <li><span class="text-huge">Login to ANVILL</span></li>
  <li><span class="text-huge">To add/edit Dictation a &quot;Speak The Words&quot; task in an existing lesson, </span><a href="../e/en/lesson" class="is-system-link"><span class="text-huge">navigate to your lesson page</span></a><span class="text-huge">. Otherwise, </span><a href="../e/en/lesson" class="is-system-link"><span class="text-huge">create a new lesson</span></a><span class="text-huge">.</span></li>
  <li><span class="text-huge">Once inside your lesson page:</span></li>
</ol><div>
</div><ul>
  <li><span class="text-huge"><strong>Add New Speak the Words Activity</strong></span><br><span class="text-huge">Click on &quot;+ Add Content.&quot;</span><br><span class="text-huge">Select &quot;Speak the Words&quot; (or<strong> &quot;</strong>Speak the Words Set&quot;<strong>) </strong>from the content menu.</span></li>
  <li><span class="text-huge"><strong>Edit Existing Speak the Words Activity</strong></span><br><span class="text-huge">Click on the green pencil above your Speak the Words activity</span><br><span class="text-huge">Select &quot;Edit&quot; from the dropdown menu.</span></li>
</ul><div>
</div><h1 id="h-2-create-speak-the-words-content" class="toc-header"><a class="toc-anchor" href="speakthewords#h-2-create-speak-the-words-content">¶</a> <span class="text-huge">2. Create &quot;Speak The Words&quot; Content</span></h1><div>
</div><h2 id="speak-the-words-tool-single-prompt" class="toc-header"><a class="toc-anchor" href="speakthewords#speak-the-words-tool-single-prompt">¶</a> <span class="text-huge">&quot;Speak The Words&quot; Tool (single prompt)</span></h2><div>
</div><ol>
  <li><span class="text-huge">Open the &apos;Speak the Words&apos; edit screen. See Section 1.1 above to learn how.</span></li>
  <li><span class="text-huge">Give your&apos; activity a title by typing over &quot;Untitled Speak the Words&quot;</span></li>
  <li><span class="text-huge">In the &quot;Describe Task&quot; box, write your question or prompt. </span><br><span class="text-huge">Ex. &quot;What is Bart Simpson&apos;s father&apos;s name?&quot;</span></li>
  <li><span class="text-huge">You can include one or more correct answers. Write the accepted answer or answers. To add more than one answer. just click &quot;Add Item&quot;. </span><br><span class="text-huge">Ex. Homer Simpson</span><br><span class="text-huge">Ex. Homer Jay Simpson</span><br><span class="text-huge">Ex. Homer</span></li>
  <li><span class="text-huge">To save your work and exit, click on the check mark icon above your Speak the Words activity</span></li>
</ol><div>
</div><h2 id="speak-the-words-set-tool-multiple-prompts" class="toc-header"><a class="toc-anchor" href="speakthewords#speak-the-words-set-tool-multiple-prompts">¶</a> <span class="text-huge">&quot;Speak the Words Set&quot; Tool (multiple prompts)</span></h2><div>
</div><ol>
  <li><span class="text-huge">Open the &apos;Speak the Words Set&apos; edit screen. See Section 1.1 above to learn how.</span></li>
  <li><span class="text-huge">Name your activity by typing over &quot;Untitled Speak the Words Set&quot;</span></li>
  <li><span class="text-huge">In the &quot;Describe Task&quot; box, write your question or prompt. </span><br><span class="text-huge">Ex. &quot;What is Bart Simpson&apos;s father&apos;s name?&quot;</span></li>
  <li><span class="text-huge">You can add one or more correct answers. To add more than one,  just click &quot;Add Item&quot;. </span><br><span class="text-huge">Ex. Homer Simpson</span><br><span class="text-huge">Ex. Homer Jay Simpson</span><br><span class="text-huge">Ex. Homer</span></li>
  <li><span class="text-huge">To create a new prompt, click the blue &quot;Add Question&quot; button.</span></li>
  <li><span class="text-huge">Click on the check mark icon above your activity to exit</span></li>
</ol><div>
